extends ../base

block content
  p Insurance company,!{' '}
    a(href="https://www.lemonade.com/" target="_blank") Lemonade
    | , sent a personalised birthday email to loyal customer, Andrew.
  p Andrew was touched and thanked them on Twitter:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lemon1.png" alt="Lemonade Insurance customer goodwill").img__100
  p Lemonade then followed up with an!{' '}
    span.italic actual birthday cake
    |!{' '} sent to Andrew's workplace:
  img(src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/harrydry/gdmarketing/lemon2.jpg" alt="Lemonade Insurance birthday cake").img__100
  p And once again, Andrew thanked them on Twitter.
  p It's fair to say Andrew's now a fan for life, but what often goes unnoticed is the!{' '}
    span.bold 2nd order benefits
    |!{' '}of delighting your customers:
  p.list.list__top • Andrew’s Twitter followers now think Lemonade is awesome
  p.list • Andrew’s co-workers, who all enjoyed a slice of cake, now think Lemonade is awesome
  p.list.list__bottom • Matthew Kobach shared this story on Twitter. His 35,000 Twitter followers now think Lemonade is awesome.
  p One delicious birthday cake.!{' '}
    |!{' '}Hundreds of new fans.
  p That's the power of delighting individual customers.
  p
    span.italic Hattip to!{' '}
      a(href="https://twitter.com/mkobach" target="_blank") Matthew Kobach's Twitter
      |!{' '}where I got this one from.
